1
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,719
What are you selling here?

2
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:40,280
What is this stuff you've got laid out?

3
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:43,400
I can't tell.

4
00:01:43,719 --> 00:01:45,239
Is it medicine?

5
00:01:46,239 --> 00:01:47,040
Doesn't look like medicine.

6
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:49,079
Doesn't look like medicine.

7
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:52,120
Then why display it on such a pretty cloth?

8
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,120
I don't think it's medicine.

9
00:01:54,359 --> 00:01:55,719
Then what is it?

10
00:01:58,719 --> 00:01:59,680
By the looks of it...

11
00:02:00,519 --> 00:02:01,719
It's cow dung.

12
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,519
You have quite an imagination.

13
00:02:03,599 --> 00:02:05,680
Who would display a pile of cow dung here?

14
00:02:06,319 --> 00:02:07,159
Don't laugh.

15
00:02:07,319 --> 00:02:09,359
I bet this is definitely cow dung.

16
00:02:09,719 --> 00:02:10,560
Brother.

17
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:12,319
You guessed right. You have a sharp eye.

18
00:02:12,319 --> 00:02:14,000
It is cow dung.

19
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,919
You're displaying cow dung here?

20
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:18,520
It is cow dung, alright.

21
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:22,360
But my cow dung is no ordinary cow dung.

22
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,680
Cow dung is just cow dung.

23
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,080
This cow dung of yours...

24
00:02:26,439 --> 00:02:28,039
What's so special about it?

25
00:02:28,319 --> 00:02:30,400
There are several kinds of cows.

26
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:33,319
There are yellow cattle, water buffalo...

27
00:02:33,639 --> 00:02:35,319
Sand cattle, bulls...

28
00:02:35,319 --> 00:02:36,919
And yaks.

29
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:39,360
The smallest is the snail.

30
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,919
The hardest to see...

31
00:02:42,039 --> 00:02:45,439
The rarest, weirdest, and most precious...

32
00:02:45,439 --> 00:02:46,919
Is the rhino.

33
00:02:47,199 --> 00:02:48,599
This dung of mine...

34
00:02:48,599 --> 00:02:50,199
Is dung pooped by a rhino.

35
00:02:50,599 --> 00:02:53,039
Rhinos come from foreign lands.

36
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:56,400
Its dung is a precious medicinal ingredient.

37
00:02:57,199 --> 00:02:59,479
So what's this thing good for?

38
00:03:00,039 --> 00:03:02,080
If you eat this...

39
00:03:02,639 --> 00:03:05,240
It reduces heat, clears heat, dispels heat, beats heat.

40
00:03:05,439 --> 00:03:07,439
Dissolves thick phlegm, removes blood stasis.

41
00:03:07,439 --> 00:03:09,960
The benefits are many, many, many.

42
00:03:10,639 --> 00:03:12,639
Soak it in wine if you have it, or urine if you don't.

43
00:03:12,639 --> 00:03:14,000
If you have neither wine nor urine...

44
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,560
Chewing it dry works too.

45
00:03:16,919 --> 00:03:19,400
This isn't rhino dung.

46
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,520
Fortune teller.

47
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,439
Don't talk nonsense.

48
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,159
This isn't ordinary rhino dung.

49
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:28,080
This dung has a mellow scent, rich in medicinal fragrance.

50
00:03:28,199 --> 00:03:30,000
It must be from Java.

51
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,400
Dung from a white rhinoceros that eats only medicinal herbs.

52
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:34,800
This is the finest of dungs.

53
00:03:36,719 --> 00:03:37,680
Right!

54
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:38,800
See that?

55
00:03:41,159 --> 00:03:42,680
Finally, an expert is here.

56
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,960
Someone who knows his stuff.

57
00:03:44,719 --> 00:03:47,039
If my family hadn't fallen on hard times...

58
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:51,039
I'd never sell this family heirloom.

59
00:03:51,919 --> 00:03:53,360
This medicine...

60
00:03:53,639 --> 00:03:56,080
I won't claim it brings the dead back to life...

61
00:03:56,479 --> 00:04:00,240
But cripples walk, mutes speak, and the blind see.

62
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:02,360
It's like Hua Tuo treating a cold...

63
00:04:02,479 --> 00:04:04,199
A piece of cake.

64
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,919
I think you're a toad yawning...

65
00:04:07,919 --> 00:04:09,280
Talking big.

66
00:04:09,439 --> 00:04:10,680
Yeah.

67
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,680
You got a shill here to put on a show.

68
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:16,080
Sprinkling pepper on a grave...

69
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:17,759
Who are you trying to fool?

70
00:04:18,199 --> 00:04:19,360
Move along, move along, everyone move along.

71
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,240
Don't go! Don't go!

72
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:23,000
How could I know him?

73
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:26,920
How about this.

74
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:30,639
If you can cure this cripple...

75
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,560
We'll believe you.

76
00:04:32,759 --> 00:04:34,680
My leg can't be cured.

77
00:04:34,879 --> 00:04:37,759
It's been like this since I was born.

78
00:04:38,279 --> 00:04:40,079
My family sought famous doctors everywhere.

79
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:42,519
Even those white-bearded doctors couldn't help.

80
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,040
See? See?

81
00:04:44,519 --> 00:04:46,120
She was born with it.

82
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,000
How could I possibly...

83
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:50,120
This...

84
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:52,199
But I can give it a try.

85
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,279
To see if it can actually be cured.

86
00:04:54,279 --> 00:04:55,800
Come, come here, come here.

87
00:04:56,279 --> 00:04:57,759
Come, come, come.

88
00:04:57,879 --> 00:05:00,240
Even if it's congenital, I can try.

89
00:05:00,439 --> 00:05:03,879
Let's see if we can fix the problem.

90
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,800
It can't be cured.

91
00:05:25,079 --> 00:05:26,759
I've been treated for years with no luck.

92
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,240
I'm leaving.

93
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,439
Why isn't it crippled anymore?

94
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,000
It really isn't crippled anymore!

95
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:38,040
I'm cured!

96
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,720
I'm actually cured!

97
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,480
I'm going to tell my grandpa!

98
00:05:42,839 --> 00:05:43,399
Grandpa!

99
00:05:43,519 --> 00:05:44,639
I'm cured!

100
00:05:57,439 --> 00:05:58,360
Not bad.

101
00:05:58,360 --> 00:06:00,079
You made so much in just a while.

102
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,079
You talked it up like magic.

103
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,680
Yesterday my nephew bought your dung and ate it.

104
00:06:10,879 --> 00:06:12,079
And today he's stiff as a board.

105
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,120
What do you have to say?

106
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,399
Yesterday?

107
00:06:16,399 --> 00:06:17,439
I wasn't even selling yesterday.

108
00:06:17,439 --> 00:06:18,439
I only got here today.

109
00:06:19,519 --> 00:06:20,199
It was you yesterday!

110
00:06:20,199 --> 00:06:21,680
He ate your dung and got poisoned to death!

111
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:23,800
It was you!

112
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:25,639
I came with him to buy it yesterday.

113
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,759
Luckily I didn't eat any.

114
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,279
Or I'd be lying here today too.

115
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,199
Listen, brothers.

116
00:06:32,399 --> 00:06:34,120
I make my money...

117
00:06:34,439 --> 00:06:36,079
...by relying on a little skill.

118
00:06:36,639 --> 00:06:38,959
Are you just trying to rob me outright?

119
00:06:44,079 --> 00:06:47,240
My surname is Fan, courtesy name Pengju.

120
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:51,360
Weiyuan Hall of Righteousness, holding the Yao rank.

121
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:54,439
What's your rank at Noble Dragon Wharf?

122
00:06:54,839 --> 00:06:56,639
I sit in your granddaddy's chair!

123
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,800
Pay up for the life! Get him!

124
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,199
Over there!

125
00:07:02,199 --> 00:07:03,600
Why did you throw this to me?

126
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:12,040
Stop!

127
00:07:15,399 --> 00:07:16,079
Chase him!

128
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,879
Take the money and run!

129
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:38,600
Something's wrong.

130
00:07:40,879 --> 00:07:41,839
Why is it all stones?

131
00:07:41,839 --> 00:07:43,079
How should I know?

132
00:07:45,439 --> 00:07:46,600
It's with that chubby kid!

133
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,160
Chase him!

134
00:07:48,879 --> 00:07:49,560
Hurry up!

135
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:54,199
Run faster!

136
00:08:03,199 --> 00:08:04,800
Heaven has a grand plan.

137
00:08:05,639 --> 00:08:07,160
Man has his petty schemes.

138
00:08:08,199 --> 00:08:09,680
You have your seven calculations.

139
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,279
I have my eight calculations.

140
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,199
Young Master.

141
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,279
My old man...

142
00:08:14,519 --> 00:08:15,600
Is he doing okay?

143
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,439
When he found you were gone...

144
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,439
...he's been in tears all day long.

145
00:08:20,759 --> 00:08:22,319
I bet he wants to skin me alive.

146
00:08:22,319 --> 00:08:23,639
And rip out my tendons.

147
00:08:25,879 --> 00:08:26,519
Young Master.

148
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,399
Just come back with me.

149
00:08:28,639 --> 00:08:30,040
Living rough out here...

150
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,879
...surviving on scams and tricks.

151
00:08:32,079 --> 00:08:33,439
How can that compare to the comfort of home?

152
00:08:34,199 --> 00:08:35,199
Take this money.

153
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:36,639
Pretend you never saw me.

154
00:08:37,839 --> 00:08:39,320
I must take you back.

155
00:08:39,759 --> 00:08:40,519
Forgive me.

156
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,320
Stop! Over there!

157
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:44,399
Run! Why aren't you running now?

158
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,399
You dare steal my prize?

159
00:08:47,399 --> 00:08:50,240
The court has no empty land, the world has no idle men.

160
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,559
Five miles across the river, ask for salt and rice first.

161
00:08:52,879 --> 00:08:54,360
You think you can just...

162
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,600
...walk away with the money so easily?

163
00:08:55,679 --> 00:08:57,320
What are you saying? I don't understand.

164
00:08:57,639 --> 00:08:59,279
You're like a shadow puppet rubbing its back...

165
00:08:59,279 --> 00:09:00,440
...your skin is itching.

166
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,360
Like a blacksmith dying with eyes open...

167
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,399
...you're just begging to be hammered!

168
00:09:03,639 --> 00:09:04,559
Hand over the money.

169
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,159
Young Master.

170
00:09:06,399 --> 00:09:07,559
Wait aside for a moment.

171
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,639
So I don't accidentally hurt you.

172
00:09:11,039 --> 00:09:11,720
Come on.

173
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,559
The money is here.

174
00:09:14,039 --> 00:09:15,039
If you have the skill...

175
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,000
...come and get it.

176
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:20,279
Get him!

177
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:48,840
Young Master

178
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,759
Young Master

179
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,480
They didn't rob me, didn't chase me.

180
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:59,559
I wouldn't have known that little bastard was tricking me.

181
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:03,559
He's been playing me like a monkey all along.

182
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:08,679
Now I'm truly a horse on a boat's bow.

183
00:10:09,279 --> 00:10:11,279
Nowhere to run.

184
00:10:11,919 --> 00:10:14,000
You've been played by that kid several times already.

185
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,919
I told you to trust me!

186
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:17,559
It's just you causing trouble here.

187
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,600
You've got my head spinning.

188
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,639
Go scram.

189
00:10:22,279 --> 00:10:23,639
Why are you chasing me away?

190
00:10:23,799 --> 00:10:25,360
If you'd let me tell your fortune earlier,

191
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:27,320
maybe things wouldn't have ended up like this.

192
00:10:27,399 --> 00:10:28,360
Are you leaving or not?

193
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,600
When I get mad, I even scare myself.

194
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,279
Stop right there.

195
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:35,639
I'm going.

196
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:40,200
Don't follow me.

197
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,639
Thank you, Brother.

198
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:52,080
Take care, Brother. Come again!

199
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:57,000
Brother, want a haircut?

200
00:10:57,759 --> 00:10:59,440
Come on, have a seat, have a seat.

201
00:11:00,279 --> 00:11:01,320
I'll give you a haircut today.

202
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:03,039
Good luck in all things, no need to worry.

203
00:11:03,159 --> 00:11:04,080
Sit tight.

204
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:08,039
Give me a shave.

205
00:11:08,399 --> 00:11:09,039
Alright.

206
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:11,080
Green hills beyond hills, towers beyond towers.

207
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,600
My shaving skills are the best in the business.

208
00:11:17,799 --> 00:11:18,240
You...

209
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,679
First, shave off my eyebrows.

210
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:21,080
What?

211
00:11:21,559 --> 00:11:22,679
Shave your eyebrows?

212
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,080
Brother,

213
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,600
don't pull my leg.

214
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:27,519
Who the hell is pulling your leg?

215
00:11:29,039 --> 00:11:29,759
Alright then.

216
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,200
You asked for it.

217
00:11:32,519 --> 00:11:33,639
If it turns out wrong...

218
00:11:33,639 --> 00:11:34,960
You talk too much.

219
00:11:38,399 --> 00:11:40,279
Brother, I'm shaving them.

220
00:11:41,279 --> 00:11:42,279
Do it.

221
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:50,159
Done, Brother. Two copper coins.

222
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:55,919
Something's not right.

223
00:11:57,399 --> 00:11:58,320
What's not right?

224
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:02,080
I look more and more like a boiled egg.

225
00:12:03,559 --> 00:12:05,039
It does look a bit like a boiled egg.

226
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,960
Why did you shave off my eyebrows?

227
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,840
You asked me to shave them!

228
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:15,519
Am I crazy?

229
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,840
Is there anyone in the world stupid enough

230
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:18,759
to tell someone

231
00:12:18,759 --> 00:12:20,759
to shave off their own eyebrows?

232
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:23,120
You've ruined my face.

233
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:25,279
That's truly wicked of you.

234
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,440
You just shouted

235
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:29,039
to have your eyebrows shaved!

236
00:12:29,159 --> 00:12:32,000
I told you to shave my hair!

237
00:12:32,639 --> 00:12:33,840
Everyone knows,

238
00:12:34,039 --> 00:12:35,840
in the Jianghu, shaving eyebrows

239
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:38,679
is a huge humiliation.

240
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:39,440
Exactly.

241
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:40,480
Make him pay up.

242
00:12:40,559 --> 00:12:41,759
Who'd dare get a haircut here now?

243
00:12:41,759 --> 00:12:42,919
Shaving off someone's eyebrows...

244
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:45,000
Your skills are just too poor.

245
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,639
Just too poor, your skills.

246
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,600
Bullying an outsider, huh?

247
00:12:49,879 --> 00:12:52,559
Is there anyone here to uphold justice?

248
00:12:52,799 --> 00:12:53,799
Looking like this,

249
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,240
how can I go meet people?

250
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:59,120
Pay up! Pay up! Pay up!

251
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:01,399
Alright, alright, alright.

252
00:13:01,679 --> 00:13:03,639
I'll pay, I'll pay.

253
00:13:04,799 --> 00:13:05,919
I won't ask for much.

254
00:13:06,759 --> 00:13:07,799
One eyebrow,

255
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,399
five copper coins.

256
00:13:09,639 --> 00:13:10,600
That's ten in total.

257
00:13:12,879 --> 00:13:13,559
Hurry up and pay.

258
00:13:13,559 --> 00:13:15,840
Pay up! Pay up! Pay up!

259
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:16,919
Just pay him.

260
00:13:16,919 --> 00:13:17,919
Hand over the money.

261
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:20,279
Just my luck running into you.

262
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,120
Want to eat?

263
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,000
Why are you haunting me?

264
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:37,480
I did a little divination.

265
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,559
And knew you'd be here.

266
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:39,799
Add a pair of chopsticks.

267
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:43,840
I didn't say I wanted to eat.

268
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:46,600
I just calculated...

269
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:48,440
That you earned ten copper coins.

270
00:13:49,639 --> 00:13:50,279
Then did you calculate...

271
00:13:50,279 --> 00:13:51,919
That I don't want to spend them right now?

272
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,919
Let's treat ourselves together.

273
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,759
Are you sure you want to eat with me?

274
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,559
Even better with some wine.

275
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:02,399
Let's go.

276
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:03,639
Alright.

277
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:12,799
Sit.

278
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,080
That belongs to someone else.

279
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:19,440
Just sit down.

280
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:21,600
Don't panic, there's chicken soup.

281
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,279
Don't rush, there's intestines.

282
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:24,360
Wait...

283
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:25,759
We can't eat other people's food.

284
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:27,080
Eat if you want.

285
00:14:27,399 --> 00:14:28,480
Leave if you don't.

286
00:14:29,039 --> 00:14:30,519
Don't you have ten coppers?

287
00:14:31,679 --> 00:14:32,639
I already told you.

288
00:14:32,639 --> 00:14:33,919
I don't want to spend them.

289
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:36,480
Eating like this...

290
00:14:36,559 --> 00:14:38,440
If we get caught, we're in trouble.

291
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:42,039
One person ordering so many dishes...

292
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:44,559
And leaving without eating...

293
00:14:45,399 --> 00:14:46,320
It's a waste.

294
00:14:47,279 --> 00:14:49,120
I call this saving food.

295
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:51,120
Serving the food! Serving the food!

296
00:14:51,519 --> 00:14:52,720
Here comes the dish!

297
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,279
Authentic Zhongjiang Black Pig Twice-Cooked Pork.

298
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,840
Here, help make some room.

299
00:15:00,919 --> 00:15:01,360
Here.

300
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:03,159
And the wine. Two taels.

301
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,039
Take your time, enjoy.

302
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:07,240
The wine isn't right.

303
00:15:08,519 --> 00:15:09,480
Is this really two taels?

304
00:15:09,679 --> 00:15:10,519
How could it not be two taels?

305
00:15:10,519 --> 00:15:11,679
We just poured it with the ladle.

306
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,799
Not right. This isn't two taels.

307
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,559
It definitely is.

308
00:15:15,759 --> 00:15:17,159
Come, come, try it.

309
00:15:17,159 --> 00:15:17,679
Try it if you don't believe me.

310
00:15:17,679 --> 00:15:18,720
Come on.

311
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,440
Drink up.

312
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:25,399
What?

313
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,039
I just went to pick someone up...

314
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:33,080
And you cleaned out my table of food.

315
00:15:36,559 --> 00:15:37,639
You even... right in front of my face...

316
00:15:37,639 --> 00:15:39,200
Ate my pig ear.

317
00:15:39,399 --> 00:15:40,279
Boss.

318
00:15:46,519 --> 00:15:47,720
Darn it.

319
00:15:47,799 --> 00:15:49,639
Mooching food off of me?

320
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,679
I think you two are mice playing with a cat.

321
00:15:51,679 --> 00:15:53,039
You won't even know how you died.

322
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,759
Boss, it's a misunderstanding.

323
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,159
We're civilized people.

324
00:15:57,399 --> 00:15:58,799
How could we be mooching?

325
00:15:59,039 --> 00:16:00,480
How could we eat for free?

326
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,799
Everyone caught says that.

327
00:16:04,519 --> 00:16:06,159
We have money.

328
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:07,159
You have money?

329
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:08,559
Then hand it over.

330
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:10,240
It's on him.

331
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:13,600
Pay up.

332
00:16:18,399 --> 00:16:18,960
You pay.

333
00:16:20,759 --> 00:16:21,639
I don't have money.

334
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:22,919
You don't have money?

335
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,080
Kill him.

336
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:28,039
Enough! Enough!

337
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:32,600
Beating taken, food eaten.

338
00:16:35,279 --> 00:16:37,960
These ten coppers should cover it, right?

339
00:16:40,679 --> 00:16:42,600
Kid, learn from your Brother.

340
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:44,080
So righteous.

341
00:16:44,519 --> 00:16:45,759
Should've taken it out sooner.

342
00:16:49,279 --> 00:16:52,440
I told you we'd get in trouble.

343
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:54,279
I didn't get in trouble.

344
00:16:55,799 --> 00:16:57,399
We shouldn't eat other people's food.

345
00:16:57,399 --> 00:16:58,960
You should have listened to me.

346
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,120
If I listened to you...

347
00:17:01,559 --> 00:17:03,120
You'd have suffered even worse.

348
00:17:05,360 --> 00:17:06,840
Little fatty, stand still.

349
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,480
Stand still, little fatty.

350
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:12,359
Where are you running off to now?

351
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,119
What?

352
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:15,640
Stand still.

353
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:18,440
Stand still.

354
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:35,680
Run, then.

355
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,000
Think you can get away?

356
00:17:38,359 --> 00:17:39,039
My money!

357
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:40,119
Give it back!

358
00:17:40,359 --> 00:17:41,160
I've been robbed!

359
00:17:41,599 --> 00:17:42,640
Didn't leave a single cent!

360
00:17:45,039 --> 00:17:47,200
You're playing games with me.

361
00:17:47,759 --> 00:17:48,759
Acting dumb, are you?

362
00:17:49,079 --> 00:17:49,759
You want more?

363
00:17:50,039 --> 00:17:50,799
What?

364
00:17:50,799 --> 00:17:51,519
Don't run!

365
00:17:52,119 --> 00:17:52,799
Stop!

366
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:58,039
Who are you?

367
00:17:58,359 --> 00:17:59,599
He's from Across the river.

368
00:18:02,279 --> 00:18:03,880
You catch up fast.

369
00:18:04,359 --> 00:18:06,000
Both of you, come with me.

370
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:06,920
Stand still.

371
00:18:07,839 --> 00:18:08,519
Come back!

372
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,640
Just a kid.

373
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,200
A little kid.

374
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,839
Why give him a hard time?

375
00:18:18,519 --> 00:18:19,400
How about this.

376
00:18:20,359 --> 00:18:22,559
We'll go one round.

377
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:26,160
If you beat me and knock me down,

378
00:18:26,599 --> 00:18:27,559
I'll go with you.

379
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,359
It's not up to you.

380
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:31,000
He's actually pretty tough.

381
00:18:31,559 --> 00:18:32,079
Maybe not.

382
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,119
Am I that weak?

383
00:18:34,119 --> 00:18:34,880
Move!

384
00:19:34,079 --> 00:19:36,279
I wasn't ready yet!

385
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,000
Playing tricks on me?

386
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:44,519
Had enough?

387
00:19:45,599 --> 00:19:47,759
Run! Run!

388
00:20:15,079 --> 00:20:16,000
Do you yield?

389
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,039
How was that?

390
00:20:23,839 --> 00:20:24,680
Not bad.

391
00:20:28,799 --> 00:20:30,599
My Old man sent him to catch me.

392
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:32,039
You saved me.

393
00:20:33,759 --> 00:20:35,039
Sent by your Old man?

394
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:37,640
You and your Old man...

395
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,599
What kind of grudge is there?

396
00:20:40,519 --> 00:20:42,400
He's posting notices everywhere to find me.

397
00:20:45,839 --> 00:20:46,640
I remember now.

398
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,680
I thought you looked familiar.

399
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:51,759
You're the one from Weiyuan...

400
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:53,240
The face on the wanted poster?

401
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:54,680
Did you see who posted it?

402
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,119
I haven't seen that yet.

403
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:58,160
I only saw "Huge Reward for Missing Son".

404
00:20:59,559 --> 00:21:00,920
If I take you back,

405
00:21:01,359 --> 00:21:02,599
I can claim the reward.

406
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:03,960
Then I'll say...

407
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,599
You kidnapped me.

408
00:21:05,839 --> 00:21:08,039
What kind of kidnapper is that dumb?

409
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,640
Walking right into a trap?

410
00:21:10,559 --> 00:21:12,240
Your Old man won't believe that.

411
00:21:15,039 --> 00:21:17,519
I had my reasons for running away.

412
00:21:18,079 --> 00:21:19,519
If you send me back,

413
00:21:20,319 --> 00:21:21,079
I don't know...

414
00:21:21,799 --> 00:21:23,680
if I'll live to see tomorrow's sun.

415
00:21:26,839 --> 00:21:28,680
Did you dig up your family's ancestral grave?

416
00:21:30,079 --> 00:21:31,279
He was marrying a concubine.

417
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,599
And in the bridal chamber,

418
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:34,960
I let loose a nest of rats.

419
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,279
You... You...

420
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,240
You deserve a beating.

421
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:43,000
You...

422
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,920
That's exactly what I would've done!

423
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,400
My mom died young.

424
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,039
And my Old man is strict.

425
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:55,240
The concubine he married...

426
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,640
Sees me as a thorn in her side.

427
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,920
Says I'm no good at studying,

428
00:22:01,759 --> 00:22:03,200
and that I'll be useless when I grow up.

429
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:07,240
She says I'm a hopeless case.

430
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:09,920
Who says?

431
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:13,000
That you have to study to be someone?

432
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:15,319
The more they say that,

433
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:17,359
the more I want to make a name for myself.

434
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:18,839
When I go back,

435
00:22:19,079 --> 00:22:20,319
I'll show them all.

436
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:23,440
What about you?

437
00:22:24,079 --> 00:22:26,079
Why did you come to this side of the river?

438
00:22:27,119 --> 00:22:28,480
It's a long story.

439
00:22:29,519 --> 00:22:30,480
The two of us...

440
00:22:31,319 --> 00:22:34,200
We're really in the same boat.

441
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:37,079
So, can you...

442
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:38,400
Let me go?

443
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:40,960
Of course.

444
00:22:41,799 --> 00:22:42,400
For real?

445
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:43,599
For real.

446
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,240
Let's go.

447
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,440
Your half

448
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:06,519
You should just keep it all

449
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:10,160
You've got a bunch of brothers to feed

450
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:12,319
Really?

451
00:23:12,759 --> 00:23:13,359
Really

452
00:23:15,079 --> 00:23:16,119
Then I'm off

453
00:23:25,079 --> 00:23:26,519
We're both from Weiyuan

454
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:29,279
Ups and downs, and fate brought us together

455
00:23:30,799 --> 00:23:32,119
In all the time I've been out here,

456
00:23:32,559 --> 00:23:33,960
you're the only good person I've met

457
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:36,160
I want to become sworn brothers with you

458
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:37,960
And call you Brother

459
00:23:43,799 --> 00:23:45,880
Since you think so highly of me, little brother,

460
00:23:46,519 --> 00:23:48,240
I must accept the honor

461
00:23:49,039 --> 00:23:49,640
Please

462
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:53,319
Today,

463
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,440
I become the Sworn Elder Brother

464
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:57,039
I become the Sworn Younger Brother

465
00:23:57,359 --> 00:23:58,799
Sworn as brothers

466
00:23:58,920 --> 00:24:00,000
Entrusting life and death to each other

467
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,240
Heaven and Earth as our witnesses

468
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:02,400
We swear never to betray this bond

469
00:24:09,799 --> 00:24:10,440
Brother

470
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:11,400
Brother

471
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:14,599
Thanks for today, Brother

472
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,359
If you ever need me in the future, Brother,

473
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:19,400
I'll be there for you, heart and soul

474
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:21,640
The Jianghu is treacherous

475
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:23,319
Let us both stay safe

476
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:25,119
We shall meet again

477
00:24:25,359 --> 00:24:26,160
We shall

478
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:55,160
You're here

479
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:57,480
Since you're here anyway

480
00:24:57,640 --> 00:24:59,160
Just sleep here together. Come on

481
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:03,359
I'd rather sleep on the curb

482
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,400
I calculated it

483
00:25:04,759 --> 00:25:06,000
There will be thunderstorms tonight

484
00:25:10,119 --> 00:25:11,240
Unbelievable

485
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:24,240
"True Madness"

486
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:28,359
I really am a bit mad

487
00:25:29,599 --> 00:25:30,599
At the critical moment,

488
00:25:31,559 --> 00:25:33,599
it's less useful than a brick

489
00:25:57,599 --> 00:25:58,200
Come on

490
00:25:58,720 --> 00:26:00,359
Give me your birth date and time

491
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,079
Just let me read your fortune once

492
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:09,200
Bingshen Year, seventh day of the third month

493
00:26:09,799 --> 00:26:10,799
Bingshen Year

494
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:13,680
You really are a Monkey

495
00:26:13,759 --> 00:26:14,720
I told you

496
00:26:14,720 --> 00:26:15,880
My sign is Sun Wukong

497
00:26:16,559 --> 00:26:18,119
I thought you were pulling my leg

498
00:26:19,039 --> 00:26:19,920
Calculate for me,

499
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,799
where my next meal is coming from

500
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:22,559
No, no, no

501
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:24,920
Your street smarts are enough to feed you

502
00:26:25,079 --> 00:26:26,960
I want to see if you have great potential

503
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:31,880
Bingshen Year, seventh of the third month

504
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:34,240
Your Sun sign is a sheep

505
00:26:35,079 --> 00:26:37,720
Moon sign is a scorpion

506
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:40,319
Rising sign is a crab

507
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:43,079
You mention these things and now I want to eat them

508
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:46,039
Very soon,

509
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:48,759
you will meet a romantic interest

510
00:26:49,799 --> 00:26:51,039
If it goes well,

511
00:26:51,359 --> 00:26:52,839
it's a good destiny

512
00:26:53,519 --> 00:26:54,599
If it goes badly,

513
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,200
it might be a bit hot to handle

514
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:59,640
Actually, your best romance is at age ninety

515
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:01,119
Ninety?

516
00:27:01,799 --> 00:27:03,920
I'm starving to death right now!

517
00:27:04,359 --> 00:27:05,599
Go climb a tree!

518
00:27:06,119 --> 00:27:07,599
"Climb" is a good word

519
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,200
You have the destiny of a vine

520
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:10,839
If you have a big tree to rely on,

521
00:27:11,359 --> 00:27:13,880
you will climb higher and higher, soaring to the sky

522
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:16,680
If there's no big tree to rely on,

523
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:18,799
you can only crawl on the ground

524
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:20,559
And easily crawl astray

525
00:27:26,079 --> 00:27:27,160
However,

526
00:27:27,559 --> 00:27:29,480
you have many tribulations in your fate

527
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:30,880
That you must overcome yourself

528
00:27:31,799 --> 00:27:33,480
Calling you a lucky star now,

529
00:27:34,079 --> 00:27:35,319
is still too early

530
00:27:37,079 --> 00:27:38,720
But I bet you're a talent

531
00:27:39,279 --> 00:27:40,680
Whether you can achieve greatness,

532
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:42,960
depends on you

533
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:54,240
Little sister

534
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,440
What are you eating?

535
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:57,160
Sesame cake

536
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:59,799
Shall I bite it into a moon for you?

537
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,039
I can do it

538
00:29:02,559 --> 00:29:03,599
Is this it?

539
00:29:06,119 --> 00:29:07,880
I'll bite it into a Pen Holder Mountain

540
00:29:08,279 --> 00:29:09,039
I can do it

541
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:11,079
Is this it?

542
00:29:12,279 --> 00:29:14,720
Do you want to see the Heavenly Dog eat the moon?

543
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:34,319
Dummy

544
00:31:36,119 --> 00:31:37,319
I'm sorry.

545
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:46,079
Don't walk on by, buy a cup.

546
00:31:46,079 --> 00:31:47,240
I guarantee once you drink it,

547
00:31:47,359 --> 00:31:49,799
you'll want another sip.

548
00:31:50,599 --> 00:31:52,119
Take a look, take a look.

549
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:06,920
Wife.

550
00:32:08,319 --> 00:32:09,960
How come you're

551
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:12,759
selling wine here?

552
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:20,440
I missed you so much.
